# Foundry RFD3 isolated runtime

Backend name: `foundry_rfd3`

This is the true Foundry RFdiffusion3 design/generation backend. It is separate
from:

```text
rfdiffusion_v1               stable RFdiffusion baseline
rfdiffusion_all_atom_legacy  legacy Baker RFDiffusionAA backend
foundry_rf3                  Foundry folding / prediction model
```

## Source

```text
Repository: https://github.com/RosettaCommons/foundry
Inspected commit: 62eba661f809120f0c5b3776837c61463e554c4c
TYL source path: ~/protein_design/repos/foundry
Package: rc-foundry
Python requirement: >=3.12
```

## Preferred Install

TYL currently lacks conda/mamba and Python 3.12 on the default PATH, so the
stack bootstraps micromamba in user space and creates an isolated environment:

```bash
cd ~/protein_design
sbatch scripts/slurm_templates/install_foundry_micromamba.sbatch
```

Expected runtime paths:

```text
Micromamba: ~/protein_design/envs/micromamba/bin/micromamba
Environment: ~/protein_design/envs/foundry-rfd3
Checkpoints: ~/protein_design/weights/foundry
Runtime note written by install job: ~/protein_design/envs/foundry_rfd3_runtime.env
```

The install job completed as Slurm job `123260` and ran:

```bash
pip install "rc-foundry[rfd3]"
foundry list-available
foundry list-installed
foundry install rfd3 --checkpoint-dir ~/protein_design/weights/foundry
```

Installed runtime:

```text
Python: 3.12.13
rc-foundry: 0.2.0
Foundry source commit inspected separately: 62eba661f809120f0c5b3776837c61463e554c4c
RFD3 checkpoint: ~/protein_design/weights/foundry/rfd3_latest.ckpt, 2.51 GB
```

The initial torch wheel resolved to `2.12.1+cu130`, which did not see the TYL
RTX 3090 GPUs under the available CUDA 12.4 driver stack. Repair job `123262`
reinstalled the CUDA 12.4 wheel:

```bash
sbatch scripts/slurm_templates/repair_foundry_torch_cuda124.sbatch
```

Final tested GPU runtime:

```text
Torch: 2.6.0+cu124
Torch CUDA runtime: 12.4
GPU test: cuda_available=True, NVIDIA GeForce RTX 3090
pip check: no broken requirements
```

## Container Fallback

The official Docker image route is:

```text
docker://rosettacommons/foundry:latest
```

On 2026-06-28, TYL DockerHub access timed out while pulling through Apptainer
job `123259`. Keep `scripts/slurm_templates/install_foundry_container.sbatch`
as a fallback for mirror/offline SIF workflows.

## Smoke Tests

Official Foundry demo:

```text
Job: 123263
Status: completed
Outputs: 3 .cif.gz structures plus metadata JSON
Path: ~/protein_design/examples/epitope_scaffold/foundry_rfd3_official_smoke_20260628_212615
```

5TPN motif scaffold smoke:

```text
Backbone job: 123264
Downstream jobs: ProteinMPNN 123265, AF3 123266, filter 123267, merge 123268
Path: ~/protein_design/examples/epitope_scaffold/foundry_rfd3_smoke_5tpn_20260628
Result: end-to-end pipeline completed; design failed filters with motif RMSD 7.62 and PAE 18.22
```

## Launch

After smoke testing passes:

```bash
BACKBONE_BACKEND=foundry_rfd3 NUM_DESIGNS=1 \
  RUN_ROOT=$PWD/foundry_rfd3_smoke \
  sbatch ~/protein_design/scripts/slurm_templates/run_backbone_generation.sbatch
```

The launcher writes RFD3 input JSON with
`scripts/make_rfd3_motif_input.py`, runs `rfd3 design`, then normalizes Foundry
outputs with `scripts/normalize_foundry_rfd3_outputs.py`.
